    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 Honda S2000 AP2, a definitive example of high-revving naturally aspirated engineering. This specimen features the longitudinally mounted F22C1 inline-four, delivering 240 hp with a seamless VTEC crossover and an 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise, short-throw six-speed manual transmission and a factory-spec Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring exceptional corner-exit traction. The chassis remains incredibly rigid, utilizing the original X-bone frame architecture and double-wishbone suspension geometry for surgical handling. Every body panel retains its original matching VIN sticker, and the undercarriage shows no signs of oxidative stress or fluid weeping. This is a mechanically transparent, turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 47250.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 19
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. No accidents. Full service history included. Clean title. Original paint and interior.",
      "price": 46500.0,
